  "is_vocab": false,
  "stimulus_html": "<p>The compound known as Hagemann’s ester is prepared by treatment of a mixture of formaldehyde and ethyl acetoacetate with base, followed by acid-catalyzed decarboxylation.</p>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdVlZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--b424f51038a4499043067929147857ed264cf319/OChem_23_EC_048.jpg\" alt=\"Ethyl acetoacetate reacts with formaldehyde in the presence of sodium ethoxide and ethanol, then hydronium ion to yield Hagemann’s ester, carbon dioxide, and ethanol.\">",
